      "description": "Available is an impeccably maintained 1997 Acura NSX-T, a masterclass in mid-engine precision. This example features the C32B 3.2L DOHC VTEC V6, boasting titanium connecting rods and a factory-spec 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a 6-speed close-ratio manual gearbox and a helical limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The all-aluminum monocoque chassis and double-wishbone suspension remain in factory-perfect alignment, offering the visceral handling characteristics the NSX is renowned for. Mechanically flawless, the engine shows no signs of weeping at the VTEC solenoids or cam seals, and the cooling system has been recently refreshed with OEM components to maintain thermal efficiency. This is a collector-grade vehicle for the discerning purist seeking a turn-key analog driving experience.",
